1
00:00:02,680 --> 00:00:03,880
What are these photos?

2
00:00:04,560 --> 00:00:05,880
Why? What's wrong with this?

3
00:00:05,960 --> 00:00:07,520
If everyone wants to know,

4
00:00:08,039 --> 00:00:11,520
I've already broken down the financial
statements. This is all the in-depth data.

5
00:00:11,600 --> 00:00:12,440
Take a look.

6
00:02:37,000 --> 00:02:40,600
Don't make me
lose more trust in you, Anong.

7
00:02:43,400 --> 00:02:46,280
What exactly are you planning to do?

8
00:02:50,560 --> 00:02:52,560
What could I possibly do?

9
00:02:54,160 --> 00:02:58,240
I've only done everything
according to what you wanted.

10
00:02:58,320 --> 00:03:01,480
You wanted Warat
to take over everything at Vanich.

11
00:03:01,560 --> 00:03:05,320
I made that happen. I've been careful
about everything. What did I do wrong?

12
00:03:05,400 --> 00:03:07,800
You were wrong
to do it behind my back, Anong.

13
00:03:09,520 --> 00:03:12,320
If you were really honest with me,

14
00:03:12,400 --> 00:03:14,200
if you genuinely meant well for me,

15
00:03:16,080 --> 00:03:19,120
you should have told me
what you were doing.

16
00:03:19,760 --> 00:03:21,880
Why are you hiding it from me?

17
00:03:23,120 --> 00:03:26,760
Take those words of yours and use them
to fool children instead, Anong.

18
00:03:45,880 --> 00:03:48,280
Don't push me to the point
of filing for divorce,

19
00:03:48,360 --> 00:03:49,280
Anong.

20
00:03:50,240 --> 00:03:51,880
You won't get a single baht

21
00:03:52,400 --> 00:03:55,440
from the Vanich family assets
that belong to me.

22
00:04:32,240 --> 00:04:35,560
This is the cooperation rate
with our new partner.

23
00:04:35,640 --> 00:04:38,000
For the department store, we estimate

24
00:04:38,080 --> 00:04:41,560
revenue will be about 20% higher
than other branches,

25
00:04:41,640 --> 00:04:44,200
since Phuket is a tourist destination,

26
00:04:44,280 --> 00:04:47,400
combined with our established reputation.

27
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:51,760
I believe this is a new stage for us,
but not a difficult one.

28
00:04:53,320 --> 00:04:55,120
- What do you think, Warat?
- Hm?

29
00:04:58,040 --> 00:04:59,120
Good. Very good.

30
00:05:01,800 --> 00:05:03,960
Mr. Jirasin, excellent work.

31
00:05:04,640 --> 00:05:07,480
You secured a partner for this project

32
00:05:07,560 --> 00:05:08,920
very smoothly.

33
00:05:10,280 --> 00:05:11,640
Thank you.

34
00:05:11,720 --> 00:05:16,240
That concludes my presentation.
I'll hand it over to Mr. Warat.

35
00:05:31,720 --> 00:05:33,720
This is the luxury hotel in Phuket.

36
00:05:45,800 --> 00:05:47,080
What are these photos?

37
00:05:47,760 --> 00:05:49,160
Why? What's wrong with this?

38
00:05:49,680 --> 00:05:56,040
I was about to commend you for securing
such a strong partner, and you

39
00:05:56,640 --> 00:05:58,480
didn't even draw
from the company's budget.

40
00:05:59,840 --> 00:06:02,080
That's right, Mr. Chatchai is on my team,

41
00:06:02,160 --> 00:06:04,320
but I wasn't aware he went there.

42
00:06:04,400 --> 00:06:05,640
Calm down.

43
00:06:06,480 --> 00:06:08,960
I haven't accused you of anything.
I even praised you.

44
00:06:12,640 --> 00:06:15,960
It's strange, though.
Ever since Mr. Chatchai

45
00:06:16,920 --> 00:06:21,440
met with that foreign funding group,

46
00:06:21,520 --> 00:06:23,200
right after

47
00:06:23,800 --> 00:06:25,320
returning to Bangkok,

48
00:06:27,120 --> 00:06:29,400
these documents were signed.

49
00:06:30,440 --> 00:06:31,400
Isn't that strange?

50
00:06:35,960 --> 00:06:39,400
It's just the normal process
for a joint investment proposal.

51
00:06:39,480 --> 00:06:40,560
Correct.

52
00:06:40,640 --> 00:06:42,320
It is normal.

53
00:06:42,400 --> 00:06:45,280
But there was another bidder,

54
00:06:46,520 --> 00:06:48,840
and projections showed our company

55
00:06:48,920 --> 00:06:51,800
could earn nearly 15% profit,

56
00:06:52,320 --> 00:06:53,400
yet you didn't choose them.

57
00:06:54,560 --> 00:06:57,440
That's what's not normal.

58
00:06:58,320 --> 00:06:59,960
If everyone wants to know,

59
00:07:00,040 --> 00:07:03,560
I've already broken down the financial
statements. This is all the in-depth data.

60
00:07:03,640 --> 00:07:04,640
Take a look.

61
00:07:08,600 --> 00:07:13,200
Well, I can explain
and clarify all of this.

62
00:07:13,280 --> 00:07:17,000
I'll have Mr. Chatchai
bring in all the details.

63
00:07:18,160 --> 00:07:20,440
Mr. Jirasin, are you joking?

64
00:07:20,520 --> 00:07:22,440
By the next board meeting,

65
00:07:22,520 --> 00:07:24,840
this project must already be finalized.

66
00:07:24,920 --> 00:07:27,960
It has to be final.
Do you understand what that means?

67
00:07:28,480 --> 00:07:30,120
You're tying Vanich's hands

68
00:07:30,920 --> 00:07:33,560
and forcing us
to accept your deal, aren't you?

69
00:07:34,200 --> 00:07:36,080
What does this mean, Sin?

70
00:07:46,040 --> 00:07:48,440
Well… It's my fault, Mom.

71
00:07:50,480 --> 00:07:52,920
I should have invited Mr. Chatchai

72
00:07:53,720 --> 00:07:55,520
to attend today's meeting.

73
00:07:56,640 --> 00:08:01,360
I'll have him video call in
to clarify everything

74
00:08:01,440 --> 00:08:02,600
right now.

75
00:08:03,880 --> 00:08:05,120
Mr. Jirasin,

76
00:08:06,040 --> 00:08:07,680
this is over.

77
00:08:07,760 --> 00:08:10,480
Everything is clear. Everyone can see it.

78
00:08:11,560 --> 00:08:13,080
You just need to suspend this project.

79
00:08:24,680 --> 00:08:25,920
I, Warat,

80
00:08:27,080 --> 00:08:28,440
as CEO,

81
00:08:30,000 --> 00:08:31,280
declare this meeting adjourned.

82
00:08:36,240 --> 00:08:38,799
Uh… Mom.

83
00:08:59,600 --> 00:09:02,480
- Mm.
- After all the menu planning,

84
00:09:02,560 --> 00:09:04,800
we end up with BBQ?

85
00:09:05,640 --> 00:09:06,480
What's wrong with it?

86
00:09:06,560 --> 00:09:09,280
I've never met anyone
who doesn't like BBQ.

87
00:09:09,360 --> 00:09:13,040
Ms. Kluayhom, you invited guests over.

88
00:09:13,120 --> 00:09:16,080
Shouldn't you prepare
something more special?

89
00:09:16,160 --> 00:09:18,320
Isn't this special enough?

90
00:09:18,400 --> 00:09:21,200
Go on, Som, tell me
what your version of special is.

91
00:09:21,920 --> 00:09:25,400
Like sous-vide dishes,

92
00:09:25,480 --> 00:09:29,360
purée, sauté,
sprinkled with fancy salt and all that.

93
00:09:29,440 --> 00:09:32,120
Oh no, you're mistaken.

94
00:09:32,200 --> 00:09:33,720
This isn't MasterChef.

95
00:09:33,800 --> 00:09:36,120
This is Chef Kluay's kitchen, BBQ edition.

96
00:09:36,200 --> 00:09:36,920
Mm.

97
00:09:37,000 --> 00:09:38,400
I don't even know if it tastes good.

98
00:09:38,480 --> 00:09:40,720
It does. Just add MSG and it's delicious.

99
00:09:49,760 --> 00:09:51,680
Seeing you smile like this

100
00:09:52,840 --> 00:09:53,840
makes me happy.

101
00:09:56,040 --> 00:09:58,120
Hurry and prep the vegetables, Som.

102
00:09:58,200 --> 00:10:00,760
Mr. Warat and Mr. Arnon
should be here soon.

103
00:10:01,280 --> 00:10:02,280
Mm.

104
00:10:04,480 --> 00:10:06,160
- Kluay.
- Hm?

105
00:10:06,240 --> 00:10:08,640
- Can I ask you something?
- What is it?

106
00:10:11,640 --> 00:10:13,520
No matter what happens,

107
00:10:15,040 --> 00:10:17,560
we'll always be sisters, right?

108
00:10:18,880 --> 00:10:21,600
Of course we will.
What kind of question is that?

109
00:10:21,680 --> 00:10:23,560
If I'm not your sister,

110
00:10:23,640 --> 00:10:26,280
should I be some cat's big sister instead?

111
00:10:26,360 --> 00:10:29,600
Or maybe the stray dog outside?

112
00:10:30,440 --> 00:10:33,240
I just want you to come back home soon.

113
00:10:41,240 --> 00:10:42,120
Som.

114
00:10:43,760 --> 00:10:45,320
What's wrong?

115
00:10:46,160 --> 00:10:47,600
Nothing.

116
00:10:49,760 --> 00:10:50,800
Som.

117
00:10:51,640 --> 00:10:53,680
Talk to me, Som.

118
00:10:54,640 --> 00:10:57,480
My eyes just sting a little.
Keep prepping.

119
00:10:57,560 --> 00:10:59,240
Can you let me see?

120
00:11:02,040 --> 00:11:03,160
Som.

121
00:11:04,440 --> 00:11:06,240
- Let me see.
- Kluay.

122
00:11:21,160 --> 00:11:22,520
What's wrong?

123
00:11:23,120 --> 00:11:24,120
Nothing.

124
00:11:32,880 --> 00:11:36,160
Did I make a mistake
by looking into Kluay's background?

125
00:11:45,760 --> 00:11:49,000
You still dare to make excuses?
Our project is on the verge of collapse.

126
00:11:49,080 --> 00:11:51,280
Who knows when Warat will shut it down?

127
00:11:51,800 --> 00:11:55,280
<i>My flight was canceled.</i>
<i>I really couldn't make it back in time.</i>

128
00:11:55,360 --> 00:11:59,600
Even if you had, what would you have done?
How would you have explained yourself?

129
00:11:59,680 --> 00:12:02,080
I want you to see how he exposed you.

130
00:12:02,160 --> 00:12:04,920
<i>That bastard used dirty tactics.</i>

131
00:12:05,000 --> 00:12:06,240
<i>I'll get back at him for sure.</i>

132
00:12:06,320 --> 00:12:08,920
I don't care how you get back at him.

133
00:12:09,000 --> 00:12:12,240
But every single baht I invested in you,
you'd better return it all!

134
00:12:12,320 --> 00:12:14,760
<i>Hey, you can't say that.</i>

135
00:12:14,840 --> 00:12:16,400
<i>Why are you blaming everything on me?</i>

136
00:12:16,480 --> 00:12:18,040
Why? What do you want?

137
00:12:19,080 --> 00:12:20,280
Hey!

138
00:12:21,760 --> 00:12:22,720
Sin.

139
00:12:42,600 --> 00:12:43,560
Sin.

140
00:12:50,800 --> 00:12:52,080
Wow.

141
00:12:52,160 --> 00:12:53,120
- Hm.
- Hey.

142
00:12:53,200 --> 00:12:56,120
This looks delicious.
Just like a restaurant.

143
00:12:56,200 --> 00:12:57,080
Right?

144
00:12:57,760 --> 00:13:00,200
Don't say that, Mom.

145
00:13:00,280 --> 00:13:02,760
- Hm?
- Som wants to open a BBQ shop.

146
00:13:02,840 --> 00:13:03,880
Dream on.

147
00:13:03,960 --> 00:13:06,800
She's just talking big.

148
00:13:06,880 --> 00:13:12,120
All we did was slice
and marinate the pork. That's it.

149
00:13:12,200 --> 00:13:14,120
Oh, why is that?

150
00:13:14,200 --> 00:13:17,880
- Why didn't you cook it yourself?
- Mm.

151
00:13:17,960 --> 00:13:19,080
Ordering it is the best, Mom.

152
00:13:19,160 --> 00:13:20,440
- Hm.
- It's easy and tasty.

153
00:13:21,640 --> 00:13:22,680
Mama Toi, hello.

154
00:13:22,760 --> 00:13:24,640
- Hello.
- Hello.

155
00:13:24,720 --> 00:13:26,040
- Hello.
- Hello.

156
00:13:27,880 --> 00:13:30,040
- Kluay. I bought this for you.
- Oh? Champagne too?

157
00:13:31,200 --> 00:13:34,160
It's called celebrating, a day of victory.

158
00:13:35,880 --> 00:13:36,840
Isn't it lovely?

159
00:13:36,920 --> 00:13:37,760
Hold on.

160
00:13:37,840 --> 00:13:41,520
I was out of the office for just one day.
Did something happen?

161
00:13:41,600 --> 00:13:42,480
A lot.

162
00:13:43,440 --> 00:13:46,400
How about this? Why don't we eat
and talk at the same time?

163
00:13:46,480 --> 00:13:48,000
It'll feel like we're watching a movie.

164
00:13:49,160 --> 00:13:51,520
- Watching what movie?
- Channel 7 HD.

165
00:14:55,120 --> 00:14:58,600
Somza? Is that you, Somza?

166
00:14:59,760 --> 00:15:01,320
You look

167
00:15:01,880 --> 00:15:03,880
so beautiful today.

168
00:15:06,400 --> 00:15:07,880
Daddy, are you drunk?

169
00:15:11,160 --> 00:15:14,000
They say drunk people don't lie.

170
00:15:14,080 --> 00:15:16,160
I won't lie.

171
00:15:17,240 --> 00:15:20,920
If it's hot, turn on the air conditioning.
If you want someone to take care of you,

172
00:15:21,000 --> 00:15:23,560
open your heart.

173
00:15:25,280 --> 00:15:29,800
There are stars in the sky,
there's sticky rice in Laos,

174
00:15:29,880 --> 00:15:32,120
an omelet on the pan,

175
00:15:32,200 --> 00:15:34,120
and in my one and only heart, only you.

176
00:15:39,000 --> 00:15:39,880
Hey!

177
00:15:40,400 --> 00:15:42,360
Trying to flirt with someone's sister?
Did you ask first?

178
00:15:42,440 --> 00:15:45,040
You know her big sis is protective?
She's got only one sister.

179
00:15:45,560 --> 00:15:48,080
Can you even take care of her
when you're this drunk? You can't.

180
00:15:50,840 --> 00:15:55,240
If you want to flirt with her,
ask her sister first.

181
00:15:57,520 --> 00:15:59,320
Who the heck is that?

182
00:16:01,880 --> 00:16:03,080
Why are you yelling?

183
00:16:08,680 --> 00:16:09,960
Hey.

184
00:16:13,720 --> 00:16:15,360
In that case…

185
00:16:17,840 --> 00:16:19,320
may I have one shot?

186
00:16:19,400 --> 00:16:21,320
Good job, boy.

187
00:16:21,400 --> 00:16:22,920
Cheers.

188
00:16:23,000 --> 00:16:24,800
Oh, it's the homeowner.

189
00:16:26,280 --> 00:16:28,480
- Hey, hey.
- Hey, Kluay.

190
00:16:29,040 --> 00:16:29,880
Careful.

191
00:16:29,960 --> 00:16:31,320
- You're drunk.
- Hey, hey.

192
00:16:31,400 --> 00:16:33,600
Alright, let's go home.

193
00:16:34,120 --> 00:16:36,960
- It's late.
- Pass me the bottle.

194
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:39,560
You said you wouldn't stay past nine.
Come on.

195
00:16:40,560 --> 00:16:43,600
- Hey, it's once in a while. See you.
- Let's go.

196
00:16:43,680 --> 00:16:45,760
Ah, I can walk.

197
00:16:49,400 --> 00:16:50,480
Wrong way.

198
00:16:51,800 --> 00:16:52,880
No, it's right.

199
00:16:53,560 --> 00:16:55,000
Our car's that way.

200
00:16:56,760 --> 00:16:59,280
I'm going to the bathroom,

201
00:16:59,360 --> 00:17:00,560
young master.

202
00:17:01,560 --> 00:17:02,400
Young master?

203
00:17:03,520 --> 00:17:06,960
Mr. Arnon must watch a lot of dramas.

204
00:17:09,839 --> 00:17:11,240
You okay, mister?

205
00:17:11,319 --> 00:17:13,200
Sure.

206
00:17:15,200 --> 00:17:16,760
You want me to go with you?

207
00:17:16,839 --> 00:17:18,839
No, I'm fine.

208
00:17:20,839 --> 00:17:21,680
Hey, hey.

209
00:17:35,960 --> 00:17:38,680
Som.

210
00:17:43,840 --> 00:17:45,480
Som.

211
00:17:46,360 --> 00:17:47,840
That was fun.

212
00:17:49,280 --> 00:17:52,760
Come on. Come on.

213
00:17:52,840 --> 00:17:53,720
Oh?

214
00:17:54,640 --> 00:17:56,640
Why aren't the lights on in this house?

215
00:17:57,160 --> 00:18:00,520
Why's the bathroom so dark?
How am I supposed to use it?

216
00:18:01,040 --> 00:18:03,040
Mr. Warat, Ms. Kluay,

217
00:18:04,000 --> 00:18:05,680
can someone turn on the light?

218
00:18:07,200 --> 00:18:10,600
Focus. Focus. I can't hold it anymore.

219
00:18:11,280 --> 00:18:12,880
I can't

220
00:18:14,000 --> 00:18:14,840
I can't hold it.

221
00:18:16,240 --> 00:18:18,240
Hey! Don't!

222
00:18:19,960 --> 00:18:22,200
Help! A ghost!

223
00:18:22,280 --> 00:18:25,720
Got you, ghost.
I'll send you to the temple.

224
00:18:25,800 --> 00:18:27,280
- Let go!
- Don't go.

225
00:18:27,360 --> 00:18:28,560
I'm taking you to the temple.

226
00:18:36,800 --> 00:18:39,120
Arnon.

227
00:18:39,920 --> 00:18:41,320
Arnon.

228
00:18:42,240 --> 00:18:46,040
The bathroom's inside the house.
What are you doing out here?

229
00:18:49,920 --> 00:18:52,040
Hey! Arnon!

230
00:18:53,080 --> 00:18:55,320
Arnon! Hey!

231
00:18:56,040 --> 00:18:56,960
What's wrong?

232
00:19:08,600 --> 00:19:09,920
- Arnon.
- Uh.

233
00:19:10,560 --> 00:19:13,000
Arnon. Arnon.

234
00:19:13,080 --> 00:19:15,080
- Can you hear me?
- Please step back. Please let us

235
00:19:15,160 --> 00:19:16,120
- take care of him.
- Arnon.

236
00:19:16,200 --> 00:19:18,240
- Som, let them work.
- Arnon.

237
00:19:18,320 --> 00:19:22,440
What is going on?
And who was that thief? I'm so confused.

238
00:19:22,520 --> 00:19:25,240
Som, we'll find out soon.
Mom and Mr. Warat

239
00:19:25,320 --> 00:19:28,400
are handling the police report. Calm down.

240
00:19:28,480 --> 00:19:31,960
I don't understand.
We were just happy a moment ago.

241
00:19:32,600 --> 00:19:33,880
It's alright.

242
00:19:38,760 --> 00:19:41,840
If there's nothing else,
please wait outside.

243
00:19:42,360 --> 00:19:45,560
The police will arrive soon
and they'll seal this area off.

244
00:19:45,640 --> 00:19:46,760
Okay.

245
00:19:51,200 --> 00:19:52,440
Uh…

246
00:19:52,520 --> 00:19:54,680
I'll go wait there.

247
00:20:18,920 --> 00:20:20,280
The filing cabinet…

248
00:20:23,320 --> 00:20:24,960
He must have taken something.

249
00:20:48,480 --> 00:20:50,000
‪BAAN SAENG WAN MAI

250
00:20:50,080 --> 00:20:52,360
When I give the signal,

251
00:20:52,880 --> 00:20:55,120
go call someone
to catch the thief there. Give it.

252
00:21:05,320 --> 00:21:06,720
Ugh!

253
00:21:07,320 --> 00:21:08,880
- Let go!
- Who sent you?

254
00:21:09,480 --> 00:21:11,400
- Let go!
- Mister!

255
00:21:11,480 --> 00:21:12,520
Mister, hurry!

256
00:21:16,520 --> 00:21:17,760
- Hey! Hey!
- Ouch!

257
00:21:17,840 --> 00:21:18,760
Let's go.

258
00:21:19,520 --> 00:21:20,640
Don't follow us.

259
00:21:24,240 --> 00:21:25,320
I've called the police.

260
00:22:17,680 --> 00:22:18,640
Sin.

261
00:22:19,240 --> 00:22:22,280
Aunt Nong. Aunt Nong, help me.

262
00:22:22,360 --> 00:22:23,320
Sin.

263
00:22:23,920 --> 00:22:25,240
- Mm.
- Sin.

264
00:22:25,320 --> 00:22:26,560
Get up, Anong.

265
00:22:29,480 --> 00:22:30,800
Sin…

266
00:22:31,800 --> 00:22:32,840
What happened to him?

267
00:22:35,080 --> 00:22:37,360
Chatchai just called

268
00:22:37,880 --> 00:22:38,760
and said that…

269
00:22:40,600 --> 00:22:42,040
Said what?

270
00:22:43,120 --> 00:22:45,000
Sin got into an accident.

271
00:22:45,640 --> 00:22:47,720
He swerved off the road.

272
00:22:49,720 --> 00:22:52,320
He's at the hospital now.

273
00:22:52,960 --> 00:22:54,280
It's serious.

274
00:22:59,120 --> 00:23:00,280
Sin…

275
00:23:07,280 --> 00:23:09,080
Turn on the lights, Mom.

276
00:23:09,160 --> 00:23:13,200
And don't be shy to have the volunteer
stay with you tonight.

277
00:23:13,800 --> 00:23:17,080
<i>What exactly are they after?</i>
<i>I don't understand.</i>

278
00:23:17,160 --> 00:23:20,120
<i>Why did he go</i>
<i>into the document storage room?</i>

279
00:23:20,200 --> 00:23:23,280
Maybe he was just a regular burglar.

280
00:23:23,360 --> 00:23:25,840
So he didn't know which room was which.

281
00:23:26,360 --> 00:23:30,720
<i>It's a shame. Mr. Warat almost caught him.</i>

282
00:23:31,240 --> 00:23:35,000
What? Mr. Warat chased the thief himself?

283
00:23:36,840 --> 00:23:39,080
I'll talk to you later, Mom.
Mr. Warat's here.

284
00:23:39,920 --> 00:23:43,040
Take care of yourself.
Som and I will be home soon.

285
00:23:45,760 --> 00:23:46,960
Mr. Warat,

286
00:23:47,040 --> 00:23:50,360
why didn't you tell me
you ran after the thief yourself?

287
00:23:51,080 --> 00:23:54,080
Why tell you? You'd just worry about me.

288
00:23:55,520 --> 00:23:57,560
Huh? Who?

289
00:23:57,640 --> 00:23:59,480
Who says I'd worry?

290
00:23:59,560 --> 00:24:03,840
I just don't want anything bad
to happen at the house.

291
00:24:05,520 --> 00:24:07,960
Fine. You're not worried.

292
00:24:09,920 --> 00:24:10,880
Ouch.

293
00:24:11,600 --> 00:24:15,280
Mr. Warat. Should you see a doctor?

294
00:24:17,120 --> 00:24:18,320
You're really not worried?

295
00:24:20,120 --> 00:24:22,000
Ugh. You scared me.

296
00:24:25,480 --> 00:24:28,080
- Is Mr. Arnon Kongkwamdee's family here?
- Yes.

297
00:24:28,160 --> 00:24:29,840
The patient has been moved to a room.

298
00:24:29,920 --> 00:24:32,720
So, no internal injuries?
He doesn't need surgery, right?

299
00:24:32,800 --> 00:24:34,680
So far, everything
is as we've informed you.

300
00:24:34,760 --> 00:24:37,560
But the doctor
will call the family in to talk shortly.

301
00:24:37,640 --> 00:24:41,280
Please sign
the transfer documents for now.

302
00:24:41,360 --> 00:24:42,400
Okay. Let's go.

303
00:24:46,840 --> 00:24:48,200
That's a relief.

304
00:24:55,600 --> 00:24:58,120
How's Sin? Is he safe?

305
00:24:58,200 --> 00:25:00,880
He's with the doctors now, ma'am.
Please stay calm.

306
00:25:00,960 --> 00:25:04,040
What happened? What happened?

307
00:25:04,120 --> 00:25:05,840
I was on the phone with him.

308
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:08,560
<i>He was driving home. Then…</i>

309
00:25:08,640 --> 00:25:10,680
<i>When I found out it was an accident, I</i>
<i>called the emergency services right away.</i>

310
00:25:12,840 --> 00:25:15,200
<i>He swerved to avoid a car</i>
<i>driving in the wrong lane</i>

311
00:25:15,280 --> 00:25:16,320
<i>and hit a light pole.</i>

312
00:25:17,320 --> 00:25:19,960
<i>Thankfully,</i>
<i>his phone signal was traceable,</i>

313
00:25:20,040 --> 00:25:21,040
<i>so help arrived in time.</i>

314
00:25:22,480 --> 00:25:24,520
<i>The doctor is doing everything</i>
<i>to help him right now.</i>

315
00:25:24,600 --> 00:25:25,480
AMBULANCE

316
00:25:25,560 --> 00:25:28,000
<i>Externally, there's nothing alarming.</i>

317
00:25:28,080 --> 00:25:32,040
<i>But he suffered a strong impact</i>
<i>to the head and is still unconscious.</i>

318
00:25:32,120 --> 00:25:34,600
<i>We're monitoring for internal bleeding.</i>

319
00:25:34,680 --> 00:25:37,320
<i>Regardless, he'll stay</i>
<i>in the ICU for observation.</i>

320
00:25:37,400 --> 00:25:40,280
<i>If he regains consciousness,</i>
<i>we'll run a CT scan again.</i>

321
00:25:44,280 --> 00:25:45,160
Sin…

322
00:25:50,640 --> 00:25:52,200
It's alright.

323
00:25:53,080 --> 00:25:54,840
Stop saying it's alright!

324
00:25:55,360 --> 00:25:57,800
You just said he's in critical condition.

325
00:25:58,800 --> 00:26:00,960
So why are you telling me it's alright?

326
00:26:01,720 --> 00:26:05,280
If you have nothing to say,
then don't speak. Be quiet!

327
00:26:11,200 --> 00:26:14,320
Uh, you have a call.
I'll go to the restroom.

328
00:26:17,360 --> 00:26:18,600
Sin…

329
00:26:22,720 --> 00:26:24,120
‪MR. RUT

330
00:26:30,240 --> 00:26:31,120
Yes?

331
00:26:31,200 --> 00:26:32,720
How is he?

332
00:26:33,480 --> 00:26:34,320
What did you say?

333
00:26:37,760 --> 00:26:40,480
I'm asking you. Sin isn't dead yet, right?

334
00:26:40,560 --> 00:26:42,560
Are you satisfied now?

335
00:26:44,080 --> 00:26:47,040
Why? Are you afraid he might not die?

336
00:26:47,120 --> 00:26:50,000
Anong, I'm asking you nicely.

337
00:26:50,080 --> 00:26:53,320
Of course.
You two fight whenever you're together.

338
00:26:54,320 --> 00:26:57,360
You must've been cursing him
morning and night, right?

339
00:26:57,440 --> 00:26:59,000
Are you satisfied now?

340
00:26:59,080 --> 00:27:02,720
Anong, I called out of concern.

341
00:27:02,800 --> 00:27:05,080
Concern that he wouldn't die?

342
00:27:07,040 --> 00:27:09,920
You? Worried about my nephew?

343
00:27:10,680 --> 00:27:11,680
You…

344
00:27:11,760 --> 00:27:14,480
You've never even said a kind word to him.

345
00:27:14,560 --> 00:27:16,520
Now you claim
you're worried about my nephew?

346
00:27:17,120 --> 00:27:18,720
Anong, Anong.

347
00:27:23,560 --> 00:27:26,480
Damn it, I just called

348
00:27:26,560 --> 00:27:29,400
to ask if you needed anything
so I could bring it over.

349
00:27:30,800 --> 00:27:32,280
Fine, then it's your problem.

350
00:27:39,440 --> 00:27:40,480
Phone ringing?

351
00:27:43,080 --> 00:27:44,400
Which phone?

352
00:27:50,920 --> 00:27:52,840
‪KAEW

353
00:27:58,720 --> 00:28:00,400
‪KAEW: CALL ME BACK IMMEDIATELY

354
00:28:00,480 --> 00:28:01,440
<i>Call me back immediately.</i>

355
00:28:07,160 --> 00:28:11,040
So, the CT scan really shows
there's bleeding in the brain, right?

356
00:28:11,120 --> 00:28:12,000
So I can explain it to his aunt.

357
00:28:12,080 --> 00:28:13,200
Uh…

358
00:28:13,280 --> 00:28:15,120
It's better
to avoid using that term for now.

359
00:28:15,200 --> 00:28:17,640
The patient support team

360
00:28:17,720 --> 00:28:18,920
will have a way to explain it.

361
00:28:21,480 --> 00:28:22,320
Sin.

362
00:28:44,960 --> 00:28:46,960
Oh, Mr. Arnon.

363
00:28:47,040 --> 00:28:49,760
You're awake? How are you feeling?
Does the wound hurt?

364
00:28:49,840 --> 00:28:51,840
- Can you sit up? Or should you go shower…
- Whoa.

365
00:28:53,160 --> 00:28:56,440
You're firing questions so fast.
Which one should I answer first?

366
00:28:57,920 --> 00:28:59,240
I'm feeling better now.

367
00:28:59,960 --> 00:29:01,880
You came this early?

368
00:29:04,360 --> 00:29:06,200
It's not early.

369
00:29:06,720 --> 00:29:07,560
It's noon.

370
00:29:09,480 --> 00:29:11,160
Oh, Mr. Warat came too,

371
00:29:11,240 --> 00:29:14,720
but he stepped out to talk to the nurse.

372
00:29:15,240 --> 00:29:16,600
I'll call the nurse for you.

373
00:29:16,680 --> 00:29:17,680
Thank you.

374
00:29:18,200 --> 00:29:19,800
Stop following me like this.

375
00:29:21,200 --> 00:29:23,480
Mr. Warat, I'm not following you.

376
00:29:23,560 --> 00:29:25,000
That's Mr. Warat's voice.

377
00:29:25,680 --> 00:29:27,400
Should I call security?

378
00:29:27,480 --> 00:29:30,920
Uh, wait. Mr. Warat, calm down.

379
00:29:31,000 --> 00:29:33,760
This is going to escalate.
I had no intention

380
00:29:34,480 --> 00:29:36,040
of following you at all.

381
00:29:36,120 --> 00:29:37,960
Let me ask you honestly,

382
00:29:38,760 --> 00:29:40,320
how long have you been following me?

383
00:29:42,040 --> 00:29:44,120
How can I explain this so you understand?

384
00:29:44,640 --> 00:29:47,320
I didn't expect
to run into you here either.

385
00:29:48,800 --> 00:29:51,160
You really seem like you want
to pick a fight with me.

386
00:29:51,680 --> 00:29:55,480
I've changed my mind. I won't call
security. I'll call the police instead.

387
00:29:56,640 --> 00:29:59,080
What exactly do you want from me? Tell me.

388
00:30:01,600 --> 00:30:03,040
I'm begging you.

389
00:30:03,840 --> 00:30:05,560
Don't speak to me like that.

390
00:30:05,640 --> 00:30:07,320
What right do you have to order me around?

391
00:30:08,440 --> 00:30:10,160
I'm the one being harassed.

392
00:30:12,480 --> 00:30:13,720
You're worked up right now.

393
00:30:14,240 --> 00:30:16,920
There's no point talking.
I'll excuse myself.

394
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:19,040
- You talk…
- Mr. Warat.

395
00:30:20,280 --> 00:30:21,320
Oh.

396
00:30:22,120 --> 00:30:23,360
Hello.

397
00:30:23,440 --> 00:30:25,320
You're all here?

398
00:30:25,840 --> 00:30:28,080
- We came to…
- Don't tell him.

399
00:30:28,160 --> 00:30:29,160
Hm?

400
00:30:30,360 --> 00:30:31,920
He's been following me the whole time.

401
00:30:32,000 --> 00:30:34,120
I told you, I wasn't following you.

402
00:30:34,200 --> 00:30:35,960
I came to visit a patient.

403
00:30:36,480 --> 00:30:37,560
That room.

404
00:30:41,320 --> 00:30:44,000
Believe it or not, miracles do exist.

405
00:30:44,080 --> 00:30:46,720
The doctor clearly said
there was bleeding in the brain,

406
00:30:46,800 --> 00:30:48,760
yet look at this, he woke up.

407
00:30:49,600 --> 00:30:52,200
Then why keep repeating bad things
over and over?

408
00:30:55,040 --> 00:30:55,880
Uh…

409
00:30:55,960 --> 00:30:57,760
Thank you so much, Doctor.

410
00:30:58,360 --> 00:31:01,320
You should praise the patient too.
He fought hard.

411
00:31:01,920 --> 00:31:04,600
Recovering this quickly
is almost unbelievable.

412
00:31:07,600 --> 00:31:10,240
Aunt Nong…

413
00:31:14,760 --> 00:31:16,600
It's okay. Please go ahead.

414
00:31:20,760 --> 00:31:22,920
- Sin.
- I'm okay now.

415
00:31:28,320 --> 00:31:31,000
- I'm here.
- I'm okay now.

416
00:31:33,800 --> 00:31:34,760
Sin.

417
00:31:35,680 --> 00:31:37,400
You came to see me last night, didn't you?

418
00:31:45,600 --> 00:31:47,760
Uh… Kitchen.

419
00:31:48,960 --> 00:31:49,800
Sin.

420
00:31:50,840 --> 00:31:52,920
It really was you.

421
00:31:53,560 --> 00:31:54,920
Thank you.

422
00:31:55,440 --> 00:31:58,600
Thank you so much.

423
00:31:58,680 --> 00:32:01,200
Thank you for listening to my prayers

424
00:32:01,280 --> 00:32:02,640
- and sparing my nephew.
- Aunt Nong.

425
00:32:02,720 --> 00:32:04,080
Thank you.

426
00:32:04,160 --> 00:32:06,040
I'm fine now, Aunt Nong.

427
00:32:07,160 --> 00:32:08,800
When you go back,

428
00:32:09,320 --> 00:32:11,120
you need to pray in gratitude.

429
00:32:12,120 --> 00:32:16,080
You must pray for me, alright?
Pray in thanks to him.

430
00:32:18,760 --> 00:32:23,040
Uh, would you like anything to eat?
I'm going downstairs.

431
00:32:27,960 --> 00:32:28,920
Here's Jirasin's room.

432
00:32:29,000 --> 00:32:30,120
Oh?

433
00:32:30,200 --> 00:32:31,440
Hello, Mr. Rut.

434
00:32:31,520 --> 00:32:33,840
- Hello.
- Please, come in.

435
00:32:34,920 --> 00:32:35,920
Oh?

436
00:32:37,040 --> 00:32:38,080
Mr. Rut.

437
00:32:38,760 --> 00:32:40,560
Sin just woke up.

438
00:32:48,000 --> 00:32:49,920
What happened to Sin?

439
00:32:52,000 --> 00:32:54,840
He was in a car accident.

440
00:32:57,720 --> 00:32:58,840
Is it fully covered?

441
00:32:59,360 --> 00:33:00,960
I can't see anything.

442
00:33:01,040 --> 00:33:04,280
Honestly, right after injections,
there's barely any swelling.

443
00:33:04,360 --> 00:33:07,080
You don't need to wear a mask
to cover your face yet.

444
00:33:07,160 --> 00:33:10,160
No, it doesn't matter if others see.
It matters if Det sees.

445
00:33:10,240 --> 00:33:13,840
If he finds out I got more injections,

446
00:33:13,920 --> 00:33:15,320
he definitely won't allow it.

447
00:33:15,400 --> 00:33:17,560
He keeps insisting I mustn't do it.

448
00:33:17,640 --> 00:33:20,520
- Mm.
- But I just need a little bit of it.

449
00:33:20,600 --> 00:33:21,440
Yes.

450
00:33:23,480 --> 00:33:25,000
Speak of the devil.

451
00:33:25,080 --> 00:33:25,920
As for this department,

452
00:33:26,000 --> 00:33:28,040
I agree with the hospital.

453
00:33:28,120 --> 00:33:29,720
The existing structure is still solid.

454
00:33:30,320 --> 00:33:32,480
It shouldn't take long,
probably not more than a month.

455
00:33:32,560 --> 00:33:34,480
- Yes.
- Well.

456
00:33:34,560 --> 00:33:37,680
You've even stepped out
to talk outside the meeting room?

457
00:33:38,680 --> 00:33:41,520
The hospital architect
was showing me the site.

458
00:33:41,600 --> 00:33:44,080
If you have something to do, go ahead.
I'll call you once I'm done.

459
00:33:44,680 --> 00:33:46,160
No problem. Please go ahead.

460
00:33:46,920 --> 00:33:49,440
If there's anything else,
you can call me anytime.

461
00:33:49,520 --> 00:33:50,920
I'll be here for a while.

462
00:33:51,440 --> 00:33:53,640
Alright, Mr. Det. Excuse me.

463
00:33:58,280 --> 00:34:00,120
You can see I'm working.

464
00:34:00,200 --> 00:34:02,160
Why are you scolding me?

465
00:34:02,720 --> 00:34:05,520
I tried to help you get off work early.

466
00:34:05,600 --> 00:34:07,600
I did good for nothing.

467
00:34:09,040 --> 00:34:11,440
I'm going to inspect
two or three more sites.

468
00:34:11,960 --> 00:34:13,080
Do you want to come with me?

469
00:34:14,000 --> 00:34:17,360
But if you do,
let me finish my work properly.

470
00:34:25,120 --> 00:34:27,040
You go work.

471
00:34:27,120 --> 00:34:29,080
I have something fun to do now.

472
00:34:30,280 --> 00:34:32,840
- Come with me, Na.
- Well.

473
00:34:32,920 --> 00:34:35,480
Now you want me to go with you?

474
00:34:36,159 --> 00:34:37,199
No.

475
00:34:37,280 --> 00:34:39,480
Why would you mess with her?

476
00:34:39,560 --> 00:34:43,080
This is a hospital. It might be
something serious. Someone may be ill.

477
00:34:43,159 --> 00:34:45,440
That's exactly why I need to meddle.

478
00:34:46,000 --> 00:34:50,760
If it's your beloved Kluay,
I'll know how to handle it properly.

479
00:34:52,600 --> 00:34:54,560
You go work.

480
00:34:55,719 --> 00:34:56,639
Oh,

481
00:34:57,400 --> 00:35:00,640
and don't you dare swing by
to see that Kluay girl.

482
00:35:59,640 --> 00:36:01,040
<i>Mortuary?</i>

483
00:36:02,080 --> 00:36:04,120
<i>Is Kluay dead?</i>

484
00:36:04,960 --> 00:36:06,160
I'll just see you off here.

485
00:36:08,080 --> 00:36:09,000
What?

486
00:36:09,520 --> 00:36:13,600
I brought you here.
Someone like you belongs in this room.

487
00:36:13,680 --> 00:36:14,960
In…

488
00:36:15,040 --> 00:36:17,080
this mortuary?

489
00:36:17,160 --> 00:36:20,120
Go where you belong. Rest in peace.

490
00:36:20,200 --> 00:36:21,480
Ghosts should stay with ghosts.

491
00:36:21,560 --> 00:36:23,360
Stop meddling with the living.

492
00:36:23,440 --> 00:36:24,280
Hey?!

493
00:36:25,920 --> 00:36:28,640
You! Hey, Som!

494
00:36:28,720 --> 00:36:30,120
Hey!

495
00:36:34,640 --> 00:36:35,760
This is getting out of hand.

496
00:36:36,720 --> 00:36:39,400
How could you let your man stab Arnon?

497
00:36:39,480 --> 00:36:42,600
Who would want that?
You're talking nonsense.

498
00:36:42,680 --> 00:36:46,240
That idiot was drunk and tried to
attack my man first, so he got stabbed.

499
00:36:46,320 --> 00:36:49,440
Shut up. No matter what,

500
00:36:49,520 --> 00:36:51,440
make sure the police investigation
doesn't lead back to me.

501
00:37:15,920 --> 00:37:18,600
<i>Once you close your eyes,</i>
<i>you don't see anything.</i>

502
00:37:18,680 --> 00:37:21,120
‪NEXT EPISODE

503
00:37:21,200 --> 00:37:21,960
Ameena.

504
00:37:23,040 --> 00:37:24,280
Get out.

505
00:37:24,360 --> 00:37:25,800
Who are you to order me?

506
00:37:25,880 --> 00:37:27,120
<i>Is this elevator yours?</i>

507
00:37:31,240 --> 00:37:34,600
Pack your things, along with Sin's,
and leave my house today.

508
00:37:34,680 --> 00:37:36,600
You can't, Mr. Rut. Mr. Rut.

509
00:37:37,640 --> 00:37:38,800
<i>I will make up for</i>

510
00:37:39,800 --> 00:37:41,720
<i>everything that destroyed your life.</i>

511
00:37:42,880 --> 00:37:45,440
It's not like that, Kluay.
It's not what you think.

512
00:37:45,520 --> 00:37:48,280
Because you're like this,
always doing things behind Ameena's back.

513
00:37:49,080 --> 00:37:50,640
<i>Holding someone else's</i>
<i>girlfriend's hand like that</i>

514
00:37:51,640 --> 00:37:52,840
<i>isn't good, Det.</i>

515
00:40:17,040 --> 00:40:19,960
‪Subtitle translation by: Panuwat Baikeawon
